The paper discusses the integration of Deep Boltzmann Machines (DBMs) into Estimation of Distribution Algorithms (EDAs) for combinatorial optimization. This involves the use of generative neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the DBM-EDA system in solving optimization problems, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of probabilistic models and optimization algorithms also relates to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of DBM-EDA to other EDAs, which falls under the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
